Involved in the design, development, programming, implementation and maintenance of large scale web-based and general application systems

Our client is Singapore's renowned brand.

WORKS SPECIFICATIONS

SCOPE OF WORK

(a) The overall scope of the works expected from the from the Contract Programmer shall include the following:-

i. Gather user requirements and prepare specifications and other relevant documentation according to the documentation standard required and etc;

ii. Design, develop, implement and maintain web-based and other applications;

vii. Arrange logistics for meetings, conferences, trainings, and other project-related events. Organise project committee meetings and prepare the necessary materials, including reports, presentations, agendas and other meeting collateral. jobs_results.title: Senior Frontend Engineer (based in Vietnam)
jobs_results.description:
The Zuhlke Opportunity.
Thrive in an environment where you can express your passion and enthusiasm for software development and be inspired by your colleagues’ enthusiasm. As a Senior Frontend Engineer, you will cooperate with interdisciplinary teams in projects and experience how technology and team spirit unite to create innovative solutions.

As part of the pioneer team, you will have the unique opportunity to be onboarded by our high performing Singapore-based colleagues for three months. On top of experiencing the sights and sounds of another vibrant city, you will also receive mentorship within teams who have diverse technical knowledge. And of course, this is only to kickstart your long-term success upon your return home.

Our reputation is fundamental to our business, so our culture emphasizes quality, reliability, and respect. We value learning new technologies and skills thus, we invest in a generous local training budget to attend conferences, participate in certified... courses, and our annual technical camp is a lot of fun.

Your Talent.
• You have a degree in computer science or an equivalent related field (bachelor's/master's).
• You have professional experience in ReactJS for at least 3-5 years.
• You have proven expertise in the JavaScript ecosystem (Es, Typescript) and frameworks like ReactJS and its ecosystem (Redux, ES6, CodePush) where you apply your in-depth knowledge to build highly responsive user interfaces or progressive web applications which integrate with REST APIs AJAX and JSON.
• You have strong knowledge in development (IDEA, Storybook), state management (Redux), and application architectures (Flux).
• You have multiple years of experience with state-of-the-art web architectures and enjoy developing modern web applications where you design, develop, and maintain code that meets requirements, is high quality, and performs efficiently and effectively to provide a great customer experience.
• You value high quality code standards, and your implementation includes best practices with considerations of performance, security, scalability, and maintainability and you want to satisfy your thirst for knowledge of the latest technologies every day.
• You have good experience with Development and Operations (DevOps), using continuous integration (CI) and continuous delivery (CD) to ship incremental improvements and have used CI/CD tools such as git, GitHub, Jira, Jenkins, or equivalents.
• You have a thorough knowledge of building and deploying Full Stack applications, including experience in automated testing frameworks like Mocha, Jest and Enzyme or similar.
• You have professional experience working in an agile development environment where you lead the collaboration within internal application stakeholders, Infrastructure team and vendors/third-party services to deliver the full lifecycle, including requirements, architecture, design, development, testing, deployment and support. Ideally, you are a certified Scrum developer or master.
• You have strong communication skills, like making decisions, believe in continual improvement and investment in your knowledge and work independently.
• As a plus, you have experience in AWS cloud engineering & implementation
• As a plus, you have good understanding of digital banking products, processes, and retail banking systems.

Life at Zuhlke.
At Zuhlke Asia you get the best of both worlds. You can leverage on the benefits of working in a stable, large, highly reputable company with a long history of success while enjoying the freedom and autonomy of working in a fast-growing start-up environment. Zuhlke offers you networked innovation power and the security of a long-running, international success story. We support your personal development with specialised workshops and active knowledge sharing among experts

jobs_results.title: Software Developer (BB-F6F70)
jobs_results.description:
GlobalTix is a comprehensive technology solutions provider to the travel trade. Today, it is the one of the largest B2B marketplace for tours and activities in Asia, linking over 2,000 partners with more than 80,000 products from 120 cities.

GlobalTix’s cloud-based and platform agnostic e-ticket distribution platform serves to connect tourist attractions and niche services with online and offline travel agents across the globe. Its integrated solution supports attraction owners’ online sales, empowering them to meet end consumers’needs via real-time bookings and the convenience of a single, all-in-one paperless ticket.

GlobalTix solution won the Best Business Innovation Award by Singapore Tourism Board. With a passionate team, we were rewarded with the 8th fastest growing companies in Singapore in 2020 and ranked 34 in Asia-Pacific.

The company, which was launched in 2014, has offices in Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand, Indonesia and Philippines. It handles more than S$150 million... worth of transactions on its platform annually. GlobalTix works with customers such as Singapore Airlines, Wildlife Reserves Singapore, Nerf Action Xperience, National Gallery Singapore, Kidzania Thailand, Escape Theme Park in Malaysia, Viator and TripAdvisor, among others.

The Role

Software Development

Be a Scrum development team member
• Ability to collaborate with team effectively
• Able to support storyboarding effort of the team
• Capability to contribute in all phases of the development cycle

Develop and enhance applications
• Development activities are expected to be carried out with minor supervision
• Able to deliver working software on time
• Able to design and develop high quality code as per standards and guidelines

Peer-Review of code
• Can perform peer-review to ensure code quality and requirements are met

Software Support

Support SIT and UAT activities
• Able to assist smooth delivery of software to SIT and UAT environments

Provide support for production
• Capable to fix assigned bugs quickly
• Able to update status and work details in Bug/Issue Tracking System

Ideal Profile
• Candidate must possess at least Bachelor's Degree/Post Graduate Diploma/Professional Degree in Computer Science/Information Technology or equivalent.
• Minimum of 2 years of experience in software development
• Possessing any of the certifications or equivalent would be an added advantage a) Certified JAVA Developer b) Certified Scrum Developer (CSD)
• Strong analytical skills, able to solve complex problem
• Good knowledge and implementation of REST APIs
• Knowledge of Agile and Scrum
• Experience with modern web technologies, HTML5, CSS3
• Experience with Javascript and frontend frameworks e.g. Angular
• Experience with JDK 1.5 and above, J2EE and Spring, Hibernate framework, Grails/Groovy
• Knowing C, C++ and C# is advantageous
• Experience with J2EE application servers GlassFish, Jetty or equivalent
• Working with Databases – MySQL, Oracle, SQL Server or equivalent
• Knowledge of Design Patterns e.g. MVC
• Familiar with source control management system such as SVN, GIT or equivalent.
• Familiar with usage of bug tracking system such as BugZilla, JIRA or equivalent.
• Experience with mobile hybrid development as well as native e.g. Cordova/Phonegap
• Able to communicate in English fluently both verbal and written

What's on Offer?
• Great work environment
• Work alongside & learn from best in class talent
• Opportunity to make a positive impact
